section.def:
claim (申索) means a claim
            made under the Regulation as regards an entry, or registration, in a subsector register
            or an Election Committee register;

objection (反對) means
            an objection made under the Regulation as regards an entry, or registration, in a
            subsector register or an Election Committee register;

subsector (界別分組) has
            the meaning assigned to it by section 11(1) of the Schedule to the
            Ordinance;

paragraph.content:
a date is prescribed in this Regulation (whether by reference to a specific
                    day of a specific month or to a day otherwise ascertainable under this
                    Regulation) or is fixed under this Regulation;

a date is prescribed by reference to a specific day of a specific month in
                    a provision (former provision) specified in column 1 of Table
                    1;

subparagraph.content:
may appear in person at the hearing and make representations to the
                        Revising Officer regarding the appeal or claim or objection concerned, as
                        the case may be;

is postponed under section 2A to or beyond the last day of
                        the period mentioned in subparagraph (i);
                        and

paragraph.content:
that the decision of the Electoral Registration Officer in respect of the
                    appeal, claim or objection is to stand under section 3(6)(a);
                    or

review a ruling made under section 3(6)(b) or (6A), and for that
                    purpose, rehear the matter wholly or in part and reverse or confirm the ruling;
                    or
